description.narrative: The objectives of the Project are to (a) strengthen energy policy and planning capacity, (b) to improve the sustainability and resilience of the electricity sector and to restore and expand access to reliable electricity services, and (c) provide financial assistance to the electricity sector in case of an emergency.

title.narrative: Offgrid access to electricity for collective uses (street lighting, schools etc.)
People provided with new or improved electricity service

actual.value: The draft audit report was shared with the Bank for comments. The audit firm is currently reviewing the Bank's comments with EDHDirectorate to finalize the report.

title.narrative: Capacity of Renewable Energy (including Hydropower) constructed or rehabilitated
Strengthening of Government's oversight capacity and transparency in sector financial flows

baseline.value: Oversight capacity is weak in utility EDH, non existent in MTPTC Ministry.

target.value: Oversight capacity strengthened.Energy Cell with clear mandate and adequately staffed.Budgetary transfers to EDH and availabilityof financial outlook monitored.

actual.value: The Energy Cell is fully operational. It is supporting implementation of the SREP and CTF projects. ANARSE is also operational.Capacity strengthening is continuing upon request. Monitoring of budgetary transfers to EDH are being posted regularly on theANARSE's website.

title.narrative: Government entity responsible for the energy sector adequately staffed

baseline.value: No Government entity exists to oversee the energy sector in Haiti

target.value: 5 permanent staff are working for this unit

actual.value: 2 permanent staff allocated to support MTPTC's Energy Cell, composed with consultants funded under the project (5 technical expertsand 3 administrative consultants).

title.narrative: Electricity sector financial model and energy sector database

baseline.value: No model exists for the sector.

actual.value: Model is utilized to prepare budget proposal to MEF (each year, in May) for incoming fiscal year, and to simulate impact ofcommercial recovery actions on EDH financial sustainability (done in March and August 2015, by EDH Financial Division). Model hasbeen updated as part of the masterplan study, linking long term prospective with tariff structure.
